<div class="col-xs-8">
<h3> How were the participants, were there youths, older people, men, women… ?</h3>
<p> «There was everything, but there were not a lot of young people, just a few. It was mostly people in their 40’s, 50’s, and 60’s. There were also many who came, I think, for... maybe like me when I first started, there was a bit of nostalgia, of the old days. You know, because we remembered hearing abenaki. But we never spoke abenaki, it was not for us anyway, it was the old people who spoke abenaki. But the music of the language stayed. Then, there are several people, like Annett, like Dolores (Annett's sister), they came and it was a bit for that I think, to remember... But among the youths, a few came by, but they weren't that much interested. They were between 14 and 19 years old. They came to a session and didn't come back afterwards. They didn't have time, they had other things to do.»</p>
</div></div>

